main event: A round object, the size of a pin head, was observed by a GOC (Ground Observer Corps) observer while on duty in the operations room.
interesting points: The object was observed while a jet aircraft was in the area.
The observer kept the object in sight until it was lost from sight near the location of the jet's approach.
The observation lasted for approximately 30 seconds.
The report indicates that there was no other report file available.
The object was described as being round in shape.
sighted object: a round object, the size of a pin head
